    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-09T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-09T03:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115/62860: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-09T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 9, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 7:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5150. American Interests—Allied Liberated Italy. Department’s 2388, July 12.<note
                        n="28" xml:id="d732fn28">Not printed.</note> Swiss report that Swiss
                    Legation Rome transmitted through Swiss Consulate Algiers message indicating it
                    continues protect American interests Allied liberated areas of Italy on basis of
                    instructions given by Swiss Foreign Office at request Allied authorities. Swiss
                    Legation Home continues pay relief qualified Americans.</p>
                <p>Swiss Foreign Office official states orally courier Bern-Algiers again
                    functioning and anticipates that documentation and relief applications submitted
                    by Americans in subject areas will be forwarded Bern via that mail channel.
                    Accordingly Swiss willing employ same channel in forwarding Legation’s relief
                    and documentation decisions.</p>
                <p>In view foregoing please instruct whether ultimate sentence Department’s telegram
                    under reference may be considered canceled.<note n="29" xml:id="d732fn29">The
                        ultimate sentence was: “Further documentation decisions involving persons in
                        liberated areas of Italy should be referred to Department.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
